{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddd68801c-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s5451"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5451"},"text":"§ 5451.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Branching","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding the Federal Deposit Insurance Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1811"},"text":"12 U.S.C. 1811","children":[],"tail":" et seq.), the Bank Holding Company Act of 1956 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1841"},"text":"12 U.S.C. 1841","children":[],"tail":" et seq.), or any other provision of Federal or State law, a savings association that becomes a bank may—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"iddd68801d-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s5451/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" continue to operate any branch or agency that the savings association operated immediately before the savings association became a bank; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"iddd68801e-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s5451/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" establish, acquire, and operate additional branches and agencies at any location within any State in which the savings association operated a branch immediately before the savings association became a bank, if the law of the State in which the branch is located, or is to be located, would permit establishment of the branch if the bank were a State bank chartered by such State.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddd68801f-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/203/tIII/s341"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–203, title III, § 341","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-07-21"},"text":"July 21, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/1540"},"text":"124 Stat. 1540","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddd688020-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddd688021-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"iddd688022-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Federal Deposit Insurance Act, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-09-21/ch967/s2"},"text":"act Sept. 21, 1950, ch. 967, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/873"},"text":"64 Stat. 873","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to chapter 16 (§ 1811 et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1811"},"text":"section 1811 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Bank Holding Company Act of 1956, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-05-09/ch240"},"text":"act May 9, 1956, ch. 240","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70/133"},"text":"70 Stat. 133","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to chapter 17 (§ 1841 et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1841"},"text":"section 1841 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"iddd688023-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"iddd688024-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section effective 1 day after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-07-21"},"text":"July 21, 2010","children":[],"tail":", except as otherwise provided, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/203/s4"},"text":"section 4 of Pub. L. 111–203","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s5301"},"text":"section 5301 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
